/target
/.spike-v0.3/
/.spike-v0.4/
__pycache__/

# cargo-fuzz transient output (fuzz/corpus/ and fuzz/Cargo.lock ARE committed).
# The root `/target` above is anchored, so the fuzz workspace's own target/
# needs its own entry. artifacts/ (crash repros) + coverage/ are transient.
fuzz/target/
fuzz/artifacts/
fuzz/coverage/

# Per-cycle scratch / session-handoff files (kickoff, handoff, phase0 artifact,
# resume, plan stash). Each scratchpad's substantive content is captured by
# the cycle's commits / agent-reports / design/FOLLOWUPS.md / memory entries;
# the dotfile copies are session-continuity scratch only and need not be
# tracked.
.*-kickoff.md
.*-handoff.md
.*-phase0-artifact.md
.*-resume.md
.*-plan-stash.md
TEMP_*

# Per-cycle local working tooling and ad-hoc coverage surveys. Never tracked
# (their conclusions land in commits / design/FOLLOWUPS.md / memory). NOTE:
# cycle-prep-recon-*.md are deliberately NOT ignored — those are committed
# in-tree while their FOLLOWUP is open, then pruned once it is resolved.
cycle-b-*
feature-coverage-survey-*.md
.claude/

# Per-cycle search-engine calibration scratch (the #28-phase-2 adaptive-cap
# cost model). The measured rates (id ~7us/cand, addr[0] 7.4us, first-10
# 75us, first-100 750us @20 threads) are captured in
# design/SPEC_bundle_md1_template_multisig_2026-06-20.md §9 + the plan;
# the .rs probes themselves are scratch (clippy-dirty, not part of the
# tracked surface). Formalizing as #[ignore] benches is a deferred plan-§9
# decision — until then, keep them out of --all-targets / CI.
crates/mnemonic-toolkit/examples/*_bench.rs
